@startuml selling-slice-class
' =====================================================================
' Spartan ERP Engine  -  Selling vertical slice  -  CLASS MODEL
' SOURCE OF TRUTH: ERPNext DocType JSON
'   C:\Users\parrg\Documents\erpnext-develop\erpnext-develop\erpnext
' Extracted 2026-06-18 from the *.json `fields[]` of each doctype.
'
' SCOPE DECISION (KISS / YAGNI):
'   This models the MINIMAL set needed for a working Sales Order:
'     Customer, Item, UOM, Currency, Company, Sales Order, Sales Order Item.
'   Each class shows the CORE fields we will build in Phase 2, NOT every
'   ERPNext field. Each class note records the FULL ERPNext field count and
'   the deferred groups, so nothing is silently dropped - truth is traceable.
'
' TYPE VOCABULARY (ERPNext fieldtype -> Postgres in the generator, Phase 1):
'   Data/Small Text/Text  -> text          Link(X)   -> text FK to X.name
'   Select[a/b]           -> text + CHECK   Table(X)  -> child rows (X.parent)
'   Currency/Float/Percent-> numeric        Check     -> boolean
'   Int                   -> integer        Date/Datetime/Time -> date/timestamp
'   "*"  after a field    = reqd (required in ERPNext)
' =====================================================================

skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor #2c3e50
  ArrowColor #2c3e50
}
skinparam stereotypeCBackgroundColor #ecf0f1
hide circle
hide empty members

' =====================================================================
' VALIDATED against Spartan Master Operations Manual v3.1 (2026-06-18).
' See docs/ops-manual-coverage.md for the full coverage map + decisions.
'
' DECISION: this engine REPLACES Ascora and becomes the JOB SPINE.
' This Selling slice is the TOOLCHAIN PROOF (Phases 1-7), built first.
'
' DEFERRED SPINE (Phase 8+, NOT modeled here yet):
'   * Job = operational parent; Sales Order becomes the QUOTE beneath it.
'   * Job carries a ~15-state custom status machine (a/b/c.2/d.1-d.5/e/f/g)
'     -- this is NOT Frappe docstatus (0/1/2); needs a first-class workflow.
'   * Status transitions are PAYMENT-GATED (5% -> measure, 45% -> sign-off,
'     mfg payment -> scheduling) via Xero integration.
'   * Multi-entity routing: Spartan VIC / Spartan ACT (job-ID prefixes).
'   * Klaes OWNS manufacturing -- ingest its lists, do not rebuild MRP.
' =====================================================================
note as N_SPINE
  **SELLING SLICE = toolchain proof (Phases 1-7).**
  The real operational spine is a **Job** with a ~15-state
  status machine (replaces Ascora) -- built in Phase 8+.
  Sales Order will be re-parented as the *quote* under Job.
  Full map: docs/ops-manual-coverage.md
end note

' ---------------------------------------------------------------------
' LIFECYCLE RUNTIME  (Phase 3) - the mini-Frappe core every doctype gets
' ---------------------------------------------------------------------
abstract class Document <<runtime>> {
  + name : text  <<PK>>
  + owner : text
  + creation : timestamp
  + modified : timestamp
  + modified_by : text
  + docstatus : int
  + idx : int
  --
  + validate() : void
  + before_save() : void
  + insert() : void
  + save() : void
}
note right of Document
  docstatus: 0 = Draft, 1 = Submitted, 2 = Cancelled
  Every persisted doctype row carries these 7 columns.
  Lifecycle order: before_validate -> validate
                   -> before_save -> insert/save
end note

abstract class SubmittableDocument <<runtime>> {
  + submit() : void
  + cancel() : void
  --
  + before_submit() : void
  + on_submit() : void
  + on_cancel() : void
}

abstract class ChildDocument <<runtime>> {
  + parent : text  <<FK->parent.name>>
  + parenttype : text
  + parentfield : text
}

Document <|-- SubmittableDocument
Document <|-- ChildDocument

' ---------------------------------------------------------------------
' MASTERS  (docstatus stays 0 - not submittable)
' ---------------------------------------------------------------------
class Currency <<master>> <<frappe-core>> {
  + currency_name : Data  <<PK>>
  + symbol : Data
  + enabled : Check
  + fraction : Data
  + smallest_currency_fraction_value : Currency
}
note bottom of Currency
  SOURCE: frappe framework (NOT in erpnext app).
  Modeled as a minimal master we seed ourselves.
end note

